\displaystyle\lim_{n \to 1}\left(n^5 - \cfrac1{n^3 - 1}\right)
n\to1\implies n\ne 1,n-1\ne 0
\lim_{ n\to 1}\frac{n^5-1}{n^3-1}=\lim_{ n\to 1}\frac{(n-1)(n^4+n^3+n^2+n+1)}{(n-1)(n^2+n+1)}=\lim_{ n\to 1 }\frac{(n^4+n^3+n^2+n+1)}{(n^2+n+1)}
x=1
\lim_{ n\to 1}\frac{n^5-1}{n^3-1}=\frac5 3
\lim_{n \to 1}\left(n^5 - \cfrac1{n^3 - 1}\right)=\lim_{n \to 1}\left(\cfrac{n^8-n^5 - 1}{n^3-1}\right)
\lim_{n \to 1^+}\left(n^5 - \cfrac1{n^3 - 1}\right)=-\infty
\lim_{n \to 1^-}\left(n^5 - \cfrac1{n^3 - 1}\right)=\infty
